            <div class="explanation">
                <h2>About XML Sitemaps</h2>
                <p>An XML sitemap is a file that lists all important pages of a website to tell search engines about the organization of its content. Search engines like Google use this file to more intelligently crawl your website.</p>
                
                <p>This sitemap includes:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>All main pages of your website</li>
                    <li>Last modification dates</li>
                    <li>Change frequency indicators</li>
                    <li>Priority levels for each page</li>
                </ul>
                
                <p>To use this sitemap:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Copy the XML code</li>
                    <li>Save it as "sitemap.xml" in your website's root directory</li>
                    <li>Submit it to Google Search Console and other search engines</li>
                </ol>
                
                <p>For a plumbing business, it's especially important to have an updated sitemap so search engines can quickly discover your service pages and emergency contact information.</p>
            </div>
            
